The paper deals with algorithms for solving the Shortest Vector Problem (SVP) and the Closest Vector Problem (CVP) on lattices, which are topics in computational geometry and algorithms (cs.CG), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of the birthday paradox, which is a common technique in cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which are relevant to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
